EmailTemplate.subject: Request for meeting: CHW Technology Platform
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Dear {!Lead.FirstName},
I work for a small Boston-based company that has been developing a mobile technology platform for CHWs, outreach workers and other community-based workers for over 10 years. While many of our project partners are overseas, we have been growing our USA work based on lessons learned implementing technology platforms for CHWs globally.
Before coming to Dimagi, I worked as a health director for a population health organization which employed CHWs. I'm a strong believer in the workforce and want to stay in touch with how it evolving across the country. I'm still involved in some workforce development efforts in Massachusetts, and want to keep learning how we can improve our technology for local organizations.
Our projects are supported by foundations, governments, universities and other organizations of all sizes. We have received multiple awards from USAID, the NIH, and the Gates Foundation to help implement technology for community-based workers.
I'd love to hear more about how your health worker projects are evolving and see if there is any potential for collaboration.
Please let me know if you or someone at your organization would be interested in a brief knowledge sharing call.
Thank you in advance for your time. Sincerely, Christina Jeffrey
Christina Jeffrey, MPH Partnerships Director, The Americas Dimagi, Inc | 585 Massachusetts Avenue Suite 3, Cambridge MA 02139 Skype: Christina.jeffrey17 USA: +1.781.799.5845 | Guatemala: +502.3195.9623 www.dimagi.com | www.commcarehq.org
